### [FAIL] [EDGE CASE] — Locale-fallback test cases miss `body.locale = ""` (empty string)
**Where:** Spec DK-7 line 53, todo.md Phase D, spec §M2a-D point 9 line 306-313
**Gap:** 7 enumerated cases: `"fr"`, `"FR"`, `"  fr  "`, missing, `null`, `"en"`, `42`. Missing: `body.locale = ""` (empty string post-trim), and `body.locale = "DE"` (uppercase de — should it match `"de"` or fall to default? `"DE".trim().toLowerCase() === "de" !== "fr"` → defaults to `"de"`, so it's correct, but not tested). Also missing: `body.locale = "fr-CH"` or `"de-CH"` (locale codes with region tags — common in real browsers).

The inline-rule says `rawLocale === "fr" ? "fr" : "de"`. `"fr-CH".trim().toLowerCase() === "fr-ch" !== "fr"` → `"de"`. That's silent-default but possibly wrong UX for a French-Swiss user.
**Implementation hazard:** A real Swiss French user submitting from a `fr-CH` browser locale gets German confirmation mail. Hidden i18n bug. Test gap means generator + reviewer never notice.
**Suggested fix:** Add to DK-7: `body.locale = ""` → `de`. Either (a) add `body.locale.startsWith("fr")` to the inline-rule (locale-prefix-match), OR (b) document explicitly: "Region-tagged locale codes (`fr-CH`, `fr-FR`) silent-default to `de`. M2b can extend with prefix-match if needed." (Decision required.)

